<section class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-body">


    <h2 class="h4">
      Usages
    </h2>


    <p class="lead">
      This component is very basic, mainly just a wrapper for the class.
      However, you can use it either inline or as a block. Both will
      produce the same result.
    </p>


    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-6">


        <h3 class="h5">Inline</h3>
          <pre>&#123;&#123;froala-content content=someFroalaContent&#125;&#125;</pre>


      </div>
      <div class="col-sm-6">


        <h3 class="h5">Block</h3>
          <pre>&#123;&#123;#froala-content&#125;&#125;
  &#123;&#123;someFroalaContent&#125;&#125;
&#123;&#123;/froala-content&#125;&#125;</pre>


      </div>
    </div>


    <p>
      Note: You can also change the element type by adjusting the <a href="https://guides.emberjs.com/v2.3.0/components/customizing-a-components-element/#toc_customizing-the-element" target="_blank">Ember Components tagName property</a>. Ex: <code>&#123;&#123;froala-content tagName="main"&#125;&#125;</code>
    </p>


  </div>{{!-- .panel-body --}}
</section>{{!-- .panel --}}
